Nigerian businessman, Obinna Iyiegbu, popularly known as Obi Cubana, has raised the alarm over the rate at which scammers use his name to defraud people on Twitter. On his Instagram page on Wednesday, the popular club owner noted that he wasn’t on Twitter but scammers use his name for fraudulent activities. Sharing a screenshot from the fake Twitter page, Obi Cubana asked his fans to help him report the page. He wrote, “Someone has been using my name on Twitter to do a lot of scams! I am not on Twitter. I am not on Twitter!! This is not me! “Obi_cubana is not on Twitter please! it’s a fake page!!! It is fraudulent!!! Please help me report this Twitter page! Thank you.” See post below:  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com